children.name: Tooltips provides additional context and clarification to an object, typically a piece of data in a visualization, but it could also be text or icon anywhere in the app. They are triggered by mousing over the object. They contain: At least one piece of data, sometimes more. Orientation, or context, for the data i.e. 3 visitors (data) visited this page between June 12 - June 18 (orientation, context) Point to the object they are referencing, such as an item on a graph To emphasize this point, other objects in the visualization might become de-emphasized when the tooltip is triggered.
children.characters:
Tooltips provides additional context and clarification to an object, typically a piece of data in a visualization, but it could also be text or icon anywhere in the app.
They are triggered by mousing over the object.
They contain:
At least one piece of data, sometimes more.
Orientation, or context, for the data
i.e. 3 visitors (data) visited this page between June 12 - June 18 (orientation, context)
Point to the object they are referencing, such as an item on a graph
To emphasize this point, other objects in the visualization might become de-emphasized when the tooltip is triggered.
